The New Mythic Dawn: The Architects of the Unmaking
Core Philosophy: The Liberation of Lorkhan
The cult in Skyrim does not view Mehrunes Dagon as a destroyer, but as the Prince of Hope. They believe, as Mankar Camoran did, that Tamriel is not a mortal plane, but a stolen Daedric Realm belonging to Lorkhan. The "Divines" (Aedra) are traitorous usurpers who betrayed Lorkhan and locked his realm into a stagnant, dying cycle of linear time and physics.
Their Goal: To shatter the "limiter" placed on the world by Akatosh and the Aedra. They want to return Nirn to the Dawn EraΓÇöa state of magical fluidity where thought shapes reality, where "mortals" regain their lost divinity as lesser Daedra, and where the "tyranny" of static existence is ended.
The Methodology: Nymic Surgery
The cultists do not just worship; they transform. Taking inspiration from Camoran's use of the Razor to reshape his own protonymic (true name), the elite members of the Skyrim cell practice Nymic Surgery.
They use lesser Daedric rituals to "cut" away parts of their mortal limitationsΓÇötheir need for sleep, their empathy, their physical fragility. This explains why high-ranking cultists like Gaelen have supernatural stats and bound armor; they have literally edited the source code of their own souls to be closer to Daedra.


Dagon Cult Session Clock: "The Unmaking" - GM Reference
Core Philosophy: The Dagon Cult seeks to complete the work Mankar Camoran began during the Oblivion Crisis. Their goal is not invasion, but transformation. By corrupting the three metaphysical "Pillars" of SkyrimΓÇöLife, Magic, and TimeΓÇöthey will create a province-wide ritual space. At the climax, they will use Mehrunes' Razor not to open a gate, but to sever Skyrim from Nirn, rewriting its natural laws and turning it into a permanent, ever-expanding pocket realm of the Deadlands.
Heroic Intervention: Destroying a "Seed of Desolation" or killing a named Dagon Cult "Prophet" postpones the next clock advancement by 2 full sessions.

Phase 1: The Sowing (Pre-Campaign to Session 12)
(This phase is already in progress when the campaign begins)
TIER 0: THE QUIET CORRUPTION
Dagon Cult Action: For years, the cult has operated in the deep shadows, patiently "tilling the soil." They have been identifying and subtly weakening sites of Aedric power across Skyrim. Their first major success was the full corruption of Thornheart Grove, a successful test of their "Seed of Desolation" artifact.
World State (As Experienced by Players in Early Adventures):
Atmosphere: Localized strangeness. Stories of sacred groves where animals no longer go, of springs that have run foul with an unnatural taint. These are dismissed as local superstitions or isolated curses.
Party's First Encounter: The "Thornheart Grove" adventure is the party's first direct confrontation with this phase. They successfully reverse the corruption, proving it is possible and marking themselves as an unforeseen variable in the cult's ancient plan.

Phase 2: The Harrowing (Sessions 13-28)
SESSION 13: TIER 1 - THE BLIGHTED HEART
Primary Actor: Gaelen the Root-Twister (Prophet of Life's End)
Dagon Cult Action: With the Dragon Crisis and Civil War providing the perfect distraction, the cult begins its assault on the first Pillar. Gaelen is dispatched to the Eldergleam Sanctuary. He begins the ritual to plant a Seed of Desolation at the heart of the great tree, intending to invert its life-giving energy into a font of blight and decay.
World State:
Atmosphere: Escalating ecological horror in Eastmarch. The corruption spreads visibly and aggressively from the Sanctuary. The woods twist, the rivers run with a faint, oily sheen, and animals become unnaturally hostile.
Social: Gaelen's sermons begin to attract desperate and disillusioned locals, who see the "cleansing fire" of Dagon as an answer to the chaos of the war and the terror of the dragons.
Party's Encounter: The "Withering of the Green" adventure. Success here is critical. If they fail, the first Pillar is corrupted, and the rest of the clock advances at an accelerated rate (all future advancements happen 2 sessions earlier).

SESSION 21: TIER 2 - THE SILENT ACADEMY
Primary Actor: Sildonia the Chanter (Prophet of Unraveling)
Dagon Cult Action: The cult targets the second Pillar: Magic. Sildonia, a master of subtle illusion and infiltration, leads a cell into the College of Winterhold. Their goal is not a direct assault, but to locate and corrupt the Eye of Magnus, a massive source of raw magicka deep within the college, using a refined, magically-attuned Seed.
World State:
Atmosphere: A sense of magical instability. Mages across Skyrim complain of spells failing unpredictably. Strange magical phenomena are reportedΓÇöillusions with no caster, wild surges of elemental energy in remote areas.
Social: The College of Winterhold becomes even more insular and paranoid. They begin restricting access, believing a rival faction (like the Thalmor or a rogue Telvanni) is attempting to sabotage them.
Party's Encounter: The party might be hired by the College to investigate the "magical disturbances," believing they are tracking a saboteur. This leads to a tense, stealth-and-investigation adventure within the College, culminating in a race to stop Sildonia's ritual deep within the Midden before she can permanently taint the Eye of Magnus.

Phase 3: The Unmaking (Sessions 29-45)
SESSION 29: TIER 3 - THE FROZEN SACRILEGE
Primary Actor: Vlagoth the Unbroken (Prophet of Timeless Chaos)
Dagon Cult Action: The assault on the final Pillar: Time. Vlagoth, a hulking Nord barbarian and fanatical Dagonist, leads a war party up the 7,000 Steps to the Throat of the World. Their goal is not to fight the Greybeards, but to find the Time-Wound itselfΓÇöthe scar in reality left by the Elder Scroll. They will attempt to plant the final, most powerful Seed of Desolation directly into the wound, corrupting the very concept of linear time at its source.
World State:
Atmosphere: Reality begins to fray. People experience moments of d├⌐j├á vu, time seems to stutter or loop for a few seconds, and ancient ghosts are seen walking the roads as if they were alive.
Conflict with Dragon Cult: This is a declaration of war. The Throat of the World is the most sacred site to the dragons. Alduin and his lieutenants will see this as the ultimate blasphemy. This triggers open warfare between the Dragon Cult and the Dagon Cult on the slopes of the mountain. Draugr and dragons will be locked in battle with Daedra and cultists.
Party's Encounter: The party, likely on their own quest for the Elder Scroll, arrives at the Throat of the World to find it a chaotic, three-way warzone. They must navigate the battle between the two apocalyptic factions to reach the summit and stop Vlagoth's ritual at the Time-Wound itself.

SESSION 37: TIER 4 - THE RED SKY
Primary Actor: The Dagon Cult High Priest (The Architect of the Unmaking)
Dagon Cult Action: The Triangulation is complete. The three corrupted Pillars (assuming the party failed to stop them) now generate a province-wide energy field. The sky over Skyrim takes on a permanent, faint crimson haze. The barrier between worlds is now critically thin.
World State:
Visual: The sky has a constant, sickly red tint. Sunsets and sunrises are unnaturally vibrant and beautiful, a horrifying aesthetic change.
Ecological: The laws of nature begin to break down. Minor Daedra (Scamps, stunted Clannfear) begin to manifest randomly in the wilderness. The corruption from the inverted sites begins to spread at an exponential rate.
Social: Mass panic. The Divines seem to have abandoned Skyrim. Doomsday prophets appear in every city. Society is on the verge of total collapse. This is the point where the world feels truly and visibly damned.

SESSION 45: TIER 5 - THE UNMAKING
Primary Actor: The Dagon Cult High Priest
Dagon Cult Action: The final ritual begins at the heart of the Triangulation (likely the Throat of the World). The High Priest will use Mehrunes' Razor to perform the Rite of Unmaking, severing Skyrim from Nirn.
World State:
Active Apocalypse: This is a countdown to the end of the world.
The Unraveling: The effects are catastrophic and immediate.
Gravity becomes unreliable in certain regions.
Time loops become common and prolonged.
The landscape begins to physically transform, with Deadlands flora appearing and rivers turning to lava.
A massive, nascent Crimson Tower begins to form at the ritual site, a spire of obsidian that grows with each passing hour.


Party's Encounter: This is the grand finale. The party must assault the ritual site, fight through the Dagon Cult's most powerful Daedric guardians and their fanatical elite, and stop the High Priest before he can make the final cut. If they fail, Skyrim is lost forever, transformed into a permanent extension of the Deadlands.

